ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid_day_raises():\n    # documents current (arguably unhandled) behavior\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        parse_french_date(\"31 fevrier 2020\")\n```\n\n**`parse_numeric_date`** (base.py:107-113) — untested. Gaps: with/without trailing time, invalid day/month values, no match.\n\n```python\nfrom base import parse_numeric_date\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22/06/2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"22/06/2019 14:30\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"no date here\", None),\n])\ndef test_parse_numeric_date(text, expected):\n    assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_invalid_raises():\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        parse_numeric_date(\"32/13/2019\")\n```\n\n**`_fetch_xml`** (base.py:48-58) — untested, and it's the one function that talks to the network directly (not via scrapling). Needs `urllib.request.urlopen` mocked. Gaps: gzip-sniffed body, stray leading newline, plain UTF-8.\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom base import _fetch_xml\nimport gzip\n\ndef _fake_response(body: bytes):\n    cm = MagicMock()\n    cm.__enter__.return_value.read.return_value = body\n    return cm\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_plain():\n    with patch(\"base.urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_fake_response(b\"<a/>\")):\n        assert _fetch_xml(\"http://x\") == \"<a/>\"\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_gzip_sniffed_despite_no_header():\n    body = gzip.compress(b\"<a/>\")\n    with patch(\"base.urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_fake_response(body)):\n        assert _fetch_xml(\"http://x\") == \"<a/>\"\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_strips_leading_newline():\n    with patch(\"base.urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_fake_response(b\"\\n<a/>\")):\n        assert _fetch_xml(\"http://x\") == \"<a/>\"\n```\n\n**`discover_sitemap_urls`** (base.py:61-87) — untested, and it's a generator with real logic worth locking down: recursive `sitemapindex`, flat `urlset`, and the namespace-stripped-`loc`-must-be-a-direct-child rule (the comment at base.py:74-77 explicitly warns against `.iter()` picking up nested `<image:loc>`).\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom base import discover_sitemap_urls\n\nINDEX_XML = \"\"\"<sitemapindex xmlns=\"x\"><sitemap><loc>http://s/a.xml</loc></sitemap></sitemapindex>\"\"\"\nLEAF_XML = \"\"\"<urlset xmlns=\"x\">\n  <url><loc>http://s/1.html</loc>\n    <image:image xmlns:image=\"y\"><image:loc>http://s/pic.jpg</image:loc></image:image>\n  </url>\n  <url><loc>http://s/2.html</loc></url>\n</urlset>\"\"\"\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_index_then_leaf():\n    responses = {\"http://s/index.xml\": INDEX_XML, \"http://s/a.xml\": LEAF_XML}\n    with patch(\"base._fetch_xml\", side_effect=lambda u: responses[u]):\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://s/index.xml\"))\n    # must NOT include the nested image:loc\n    assert urls == [\"http://s/1.html\", \"http://s/2.html\"]\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_flat_urlset_only():\n    with patch(\"base._fetch_xml\", return_value=LEAF_XML):\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://s/flat.xml\"))\n    assert urls == [\"http://s/1.html\", \"http://s/2.html\"]\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_lazy_generator():\n    # caller can stop early without fetching every sub-sitemap\n    calls = []\n    def fake_fetch(u):\n        calls.append(u)\n        return INDEX_XML if u == \"http://s/index.xml\" else LEAF_XML\n    with patch(\"base._fetch_xml\", side_effect=fake_fetch):\n        gen = discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://s/index.xml\")\n        next(gen)  # only pulls the first leaf URL\n    assert calls == [\"http://s/index.xml\", \"http://s/a.xml\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `base.py` — `NewsSource` (the whole crawl pipeline is untested)\n\nSuggested `conftest.py` fixture:\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport base\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef isolated_dirs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"STATE_DIR\", tmp_path / \"state\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"DATA_DIR\", tmp_path / \"data\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"LOG_DIR\", tmp_path / \"logs\")\n    return tmp_path\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef fake_source(isolated_dirs):\n    from models import SiteSelectors\n    class FakeSource(base.NewsSource):\n        source_name = \"fake\"\n        selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\", author=\"a.byline\")\n    return FakeSource()\n```\n\n**State persistence** — `_load_state`/`_save_state` (base.py:138-149): untested. Gaps: missing file → default dict, existing file round-trips, atomic replace (tmp file doesn't leak on success).\n\n```python\ndef test_load_state_missing_file_returns_default(fake_source):\n    assert fake_source._load_state() == {\"seen_urls\": [], \"total_saved\": 0}\n\ndef test_save_then_load_state_roundtrip(fake_source):\n    fake_source._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"a\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n    assert fake_source._load_state() == {\"seen_urls\": [\"a\"], \"total_saved\": 1}\n\ndef test_save_state_no_leftover_tmp_file(fake_source):\n    fake_source._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [], \"total_saved\": 0})\n    assert not fake_source._state_path.with_suffix(\".json.tmp\").exists()\n```\n\n**`list_article_urls` default/NotImplementedError** (base.py:167-172) — untested branch: a subclass with no `sitemap_url` and no override must raise.\n\n```python\ndef test_list_article_urls_without_sitemap_raises(isolated_dirs):\n    from models import SiteSelectors\n    class NoSitemap(base.NewsSource):\n        source_name = \"no-sitemap\"\n        selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n    with pytest.raises(NotImplementedError):\n        list(NoSitemap().list_article_urls())\n```\n\n**`parse_article`** (base.py:174-243) — the biggest untested surface. It needs a fake \"page\" object matching the scrapling `Adaptor` interface (`.css(sel)` → iterable with `.first`, `.get_all_text(strip=True)`, `.attrib.get(...)`). Build fixtures either with `scrapling.parser.Adaptor(html_string)` directly (fastest, most realistic) or a hand-rolled stub if that import proves awkward — worth a quick spike before committing to one approach.\n\nGaps to cover, each currently untested:\n- title selector matches nothing → `parse_article` returns `None` (and the caller in `crawl()` marks the URL seen forever — see below).\n- `author=None` in selectors → `author` stays `None` without ever calling `.css`.\n- author selector present but matches nothing → `None`.\n- `published_date_attr` set → reads attribute, not text.\n- `published_date_format=\"french\"` / `\"numeric\"` → dispatches to the right parser.\n- `published_date_format=None` with a selector but no attr → falls back to raw text.\n- no `published_date` selector at all → `None`.\n- `embed_url`: iframe present and non-`about:blank` wins; `iframe src=\"about:blank\"` is skipped and falls through to `<video><source>`; neither present → `None`.\n- `cover_image` from `og:image` meta, absent → `None`.\n- `_extract_images`: dedup across repeated URLs, `data:` URIs skipped, `data-src` preferred over `src` (lazy-load), relative URLs resolved via `urljoin`, cover image included first.\n\n```python\ndef test_parse_article_returns_none_when_title_missing(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    fake_page = build_fake_page(\"<html><body><p>no title here</p></body></html>\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"fetch\", lambda url: fake_page)\n    assert fake_source.parse_article(\"http://x/1\") is None\n\ndef test_parse_article_full_happy_path(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    html = \"\"\"\n    <html><body>\n      <h1>My Title</h1>\n      <p>Para one.</p><p>Para two.</p>\n      <a class=\"byline\">Jane Doe</a>\n      <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"http://x/cover.jpg\">\n      <iframe src=\"about:blank\"></iframe>\n      <iframe src=\"http://embed/1\"></iframe>\n      <figure><img data-src=\"/imgs/a.jpg\" src=\"/placeholder.gif\"></figure>\n    </body></html>\"\"\"\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"fetch\", lambda url: build_fake_page(html))\n    article = fake_source.parse_article(\"http://x/1\")\n    assert article.title == \"My Title\"\n    assert article.body == \"Para one.\\n\\nPara two.\"\n    assert article.author == \"Jane Doe\"\n    assert article.cover_image == \"http://x/cover.jpg\"\n    assert article.embed_url == \"http://embed/1\"          # about:blank skipped\n    assert article.images[0] == \"http://x/cover.jpg\"       # cover first\n    assert \"http://x/imgs/a.jpg\" in article.images         # data-src over src, resolved\n```\n\n**`crawl()`** (base.py:273-333) — the entire orchestration logic is untested. This is the most important test target in the whole app. Key scenarios:\n\n```python\ndef test_crawl_skips_already_seen_urls(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    fake_source._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"http://x/1\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([\"http://x/1\", \"http://x/2\"]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    saved = fake_source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert [a.url for a in saved] == [\"http://x/2\"]\n\ndef test_crawl_respects_limit(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([f\"http://x/{i}\" for i in range(5)]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    saved = fake_source.crawl(limit=2)\n    assert len(saved) == 2\n    assert fake_source._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"limit reached\"\n\ndef test_crawl_unlimited_when_limit_zero_or_negative(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([f\"http://x/{i}\" for i in range(3)]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    saved = fake_source.crawl(limit=0)\n    assert len(saved) == 3\n    assert fake_source._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"exhausted\"\n\ndef test_crawl_parse_error_is_logged_and_url_stays_retryable(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    def flaky_parse(url):\n        raise RuntimeError(\"network blip\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([\"http://x/1\"]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", flaky_parse)\n    saved = fake_source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []\n    # NOT marked seen -> eligible for retry next run\n    assert \"http://x/1\" not in fake_source._load_state().get(\"seen_urls\", [])\n    assert \"error fetching\" in fake_source._log_path.read_text()\n\ndef test_crawl_non_article_page_is_marked_seen_forever(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([\"http://x/1\"]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: None)  # title didn't match\n    saved = fake_source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []\n    assert \"http://x/1\" in fake_source._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"]\n\ndef test_crawl_discovery_failure_persists_state_then_reraises(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    def boom():\n        yield \"http://x/1\"\n        raise ConnectionError(\"discovery down\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", boom)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    with pytest.raises(ConnectionError):\n        fake_source.crawl(limit=10)\n    state = fake_source._load_state()\n    assert state[\"last_stopped_reason\"].startswith(\"error:\")\n    assert \"http://x/1\" in state[\"seen_urls\"]  # already-saved article survives the crash\n\ndef test_crawl_on_save_callback_invoked_per_article(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([\"http://x/1\", \"http://x/2\"]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    seen = []\n    fake_source.crawl(limit=10, on_save=seen.append)\n    assert [a.url for a in seen] == [\"http://x/1\", \"http://x/2\"]\n\ndef test_crawl_appends_jsonl_and_increments_total_saved(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"list_article_urls\", lambda: iter([\"http://x/1\"]))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fake_source, \"parse_article\", lambda u: make_article(u))\n    fake_source.crawl(limit=10)\n    lines = fake_source._data_path.read_text().splitlines()\n    assert len(lines) == 1\n    assert fake_source._load_state()[\"total_saved\"] == 1\n```\n\n**`fetch()`** (base.py:162-165) — untested branch: `needs_stealth=True` routes through `StealthyFetcher.fetch`, otherwise `Fetcher.get`.\n\n```python\ndef test_fetch_uses_stealthy_fetcher_when_flagged(fake_source, monkeypatch):\n    fake_source.needs_stealth = True\n    with patch(\"base.StealthyFetcher.fetch\") as m:\n        fake_source.fetch(\"http://x\")\n        m.assert_called_once_with(\"http://x\")\n\ndef test_fetch_uses_plain_fetcher_by_default(fake_source):\n    with patch(\"base.Fetcher.get\") as m:\n        fake_source.fetch(\"http://x\")\n        m.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `providers.py` — provider-specific overrides (0% covered)\n\n**`MadagascarTribune._is_article_link`** (providers.py:69-77) — pure static method, cheap to fully cover; currently has zero tests despite 5 distinct rejection rules.\n\n```python\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n    (None, False),\n    (\"article.html\", True),\n    (\"article.htm\", False),                     # wrong extension\n    (\"rubrique-.html\", False),                   # category convention\n    (\"http://other.com/a.html\", False),          # absolute\n    (\"/a.html\", False),                          # root-relative\n    (\"_JaneDoe,123_.html\", False),                # author page\n])\ndef test_is_article_link(href, expected):\n    assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n```\n\n**`MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` / `_discover_categories`** (providers.py:62-103) — untested. Needs `Fetcher.get` mocked. Gaps: category discovery via `rubrique` regex + dedup + numeric sort, pagination stopping when `new_on_page == 0`, redirect handling (`page_url = page.url`).\n\n**`FreeNews.list_article_urls`** (providers.py:165-183) — untested. Gaps: pagination continues while `posts` non-empty, stops cleanly on HTTP 400 (`rest_post_invalid_page_number`), **re-raises any other `HTTPError`** (currently untested — worth confirming this is intended, since a transient 500 would abort the whole crawl rather than retry).\n\n```python\nimport urllib.error\nfrom providers import FreeNews\n\ndef test_freenews_stops_on_400(monkeypatch):\n    def fake_urlopen(req, timeout=20):\n        raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 400, \"bad page\", None, None)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\", fake_urlopen)\n    assert list(FreeNews().list_article_urls()) == []\n\ndef test_freenews_reraises_non_400_http_error(monkeypatch):\n    def fake_urlopen(req, timeout=20):\n        raise urllib.error.HTTPError(req.full_url, 500, \"boom\", None, None)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\", fake_urlopen)\n    with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n        list(FreeNews().list_article_urls())\n```\n\n**`Moov.list_article_urls`** (providers.py:204-228) — untested BFS spider. Gaps: `enqueue` dedup via `queued`, filters to links containing `/article/`, frontier expansion failure is **silently swallowed** (`except Exception: continue` at providers.py:225-226) — this broad catch has no test and could mask real bugs (e.g. a bad selector silently truncating the crawl instead of surfacing).\n\n```python\ndef test_moov_frontier_expansion_failure_does_not_abort_crawl(monkeypatch):\n    # home page yields two article links; second page's fetch raises but crawl continues\n    ...\n```\n\n**`PROVIDERS` registry** (providers.py:271-283) — untested integrity check: every value is a `NewsSource` subclass, every class defines `source_name` and `selectors`, and either `sitemap_url` or an overridden `list_article_urls`.\n\n```python\nfrom providers import PROVIDERS\nfrom base import NewsSource\n\ndef test_all_providers_are_news_source_subclasses():\n    for name, cls in PROVIDERS.items():\n        assert issubclass(cls, NewsSource)\n        assert cls.source_name == name  # catches copy-paste key/attr mismatches\n\ndef test_all_providers_have_sitemap_or_override():\n    base_method = NewsSource.list_article_urls\n    for cls in PROVIDERS.values():\n        assert cls.sitemap_url is not None or cls.list_article_urls is not base_method\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `models.py` — low risk but zero coverage\n\nMainly a regression guard against the classic mutable-default-argument bug (already avoided correctly via `field(default_factory=list)`, but worth locking in):\n\n```python\nfrom models import Article\n\ndef test_article_images_default_not_shared_between_instances():\n    a = Article(url=\"1\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n    b = Article(url=\"2\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n    a.images.append(\"x\")\n    assert b.images == []\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `main.py` — CLI, integration-level, currently untested\n\nGaps: `--provider all` expands to every registered provider name in order; a single provider name runs only that one; `--limit` default is 10 and is forwarded to `crawl()`; the `on_save` lambda formats `title!r` and `published_date` for stdout.\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport main\n\ndef test_main_all_runs_every_provider(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"prog\", \"all\", \"--limit\", \"5\"])\n    fake_cls = MagicMock()\n    fake_cls.return_value.crawl.return_value = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(main, \"PROVIDERS\", {\"p1\": fake_cls, \"p2\": fake_cls})\n    main.main()\n    assert fake_cls.return_value.crawl.call_count == 2\n    fake_cls.return_value.crawl.assert_called_with(limit=5, on_save=pytest.approx(None) if False else fake_cls.return_value.crawl.call_args.kwargs[\"on_save\"])\n\ndef test_main_single_provider_runs_only_that_one(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"prog\", \"p1\"])\n    fake_cls = MagicMock()\n    other_cls = MagicMock()\n    fake_cls.return_value.crawl.return_value = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(main, \"PROVIDERS\", {\"p1\": fake_cls, \"p2\": other_cls})\n    main.main()\n    fake_cls.return_value.crawl.assert_called_once()\n    other_cls.assert_not_called()\n```\n\n(For a true CLI smoke test, `run` skill / subprocess invocation with `--limit 0` against a stubbed provider would also work — but the above unit-level mock is enough to cover the argument wiring.)\n\n---\n\n### Summary of gaps by category\n\n| Category | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Untested functions/classes | All of them — 0 test files exist |\n| Edge cases (date parsing, sitemap XML structure, image extraction) | None covered |\n| Missing error-handling tests | `_fetch_xml` failures, `parse_article` exceptions in `crawl()`, discovery-level exception + re-raise, FreeNews non-400 `HTTPError`, Moov's swallowed frontier-fetch exceptions |\n| Integration/E2E | No test exercises `crawl()` end-to-end (resumability across two calls, JSONL + state file correctness), no CLI test, no registry-integrity test, no fixture-based \"does this provider's selectors still match real HTML\" contract test |\n\n**Recommended layout**: `apps/crawler/tests/{conftest.py, test_base.py, test_providers.py, test_models.py, test_main.py}`, using `monkeypatch` for the `STATE_DIR`/`DATA_DIR`/`LOG_DIR` redirection and for `Fetcher`/`StealthyFetcher`/`urllib.request.urlopen`, plus a small `build_fake_page(html)` helper (likely `scrapling.parser.Adaptor(html)` — worth a quick spike to confirm the import path) 